Through the carnival of death Hood has sent his Texans and Georgians at a run-their wild yells rending the dull roar of the fight;
their bayonets flashing in a jagged line of light like hungry teeth!
Jackson has swung gradually round the enemy's right; and Stephen Lee's artillery has advanced from the center-ever tearing and crashing through the Federal ranks, scattering terror and death in its unswerving path!

This was a service of keen excitement and constant danger;
demanding clear heads and iron nerves.
Both were forthcoming, especially from navy volunteers; and many were the hair-breadth ‘scapes that made the names of Maffit, Wilkinson and their confreres, household words among the rough sea-dogs of Wilmington.
